# Memory Evolution

Project memory lives in `docs/memory/`. Update it so future AI sessions start with accurate context.

## When to update

| Trigger | Update |
|---------|--------|
| Feature completed | `STATE.md` + feature spec status |
| New recurring pattern | `PATTERNS.md` |
| Architecture/trade-off choice | `DECISIONS.md` |
| Spec drift (code ≠ spec) | Fix spec or code, then `STATE.md` |
| Deprecated feature | Mark `deprecated` in spec + STATE |

## STATE.md rules
- List only **implemented** files/features
- One line per item: `path — purpose`
- Separate sections: Client, Server, API, WebSocket
- Mark planned items explicitly as `planned:` prefix

## DECISIONS.md format (ADR-lite)
```markdown
## ADR-NNN: Title
**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD | **Status:** accepted
**Context:** ...
**Decision:** ...
**Consequences:** ...
```

## PATTERNS.md rules
- Copy-pasteable examples from real codebase
- Tag with area: `[client]`, `[server]`, `[api]`, `[socket]`
- Remove patterns that no longer apply

## Do NOT
- Duplicate AGENTS.md or SPEC.md content
- Store secrets or .env values
- Write verbose prose — keep entries scannable

Use skill `update-memory` after significant changes.
